# Tasks: Control Structure Extensions

**Input**: Design documents from `/specs/001-control-structure-extension/`
**Prerequisites**: plan.md, spec.md, research.md, data-model.md, contracts/

**Tests**: Constitution VII mandates TDD - tests MUST be written before implementation.

**Organization**: Tasks grouped by user story for independent implementation.

## Format: `[ID] [P?] [Story] Description`

- **[P]**: Can run in parallel (different files, no dependencies)
- **[Story]**: Which user story this task belongs to (US1-US4)
- Exact file paths included in descriptions

## Path Conventions

```text
src/clysm/compiler/ast.lisp           # AST definitions and parsing
src/clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section.lisp  # Wasm codegen
tests/contract/                       # Contract tests
tests/unit/                           # Unit tests
```

---

## Phase 1: Setup

**Purpose**: Prepare development environment and understand current state

- [ ] T001 Review existing `values` implementation at `src/clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section.lisp:12930-12981`
- [ ] T002 Review existing `the` implementation at `src/clysm/compiler/ast.lisp:825-830`
- [ ] T003 [P] Review existing `labels` implementation at `src/clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section.lisp:6459-6580`
- [ ] T004 [P] Review `parse-compound-form` dispatch at `src/clysm/compiler/ast.lisp`

---

## Phase 2: Foundational (Blocking Prerequisites)

**Purpose**: Infrastructure required by User Story 4 (handler-case)

**âš ï¸ CRITICAL**: handler-case (US4) requires new AST infrastructure

- [ ] T005 Define `handler-clause` struct in `src/clysm/compiler/ast.lisp`

- [ ] T007 Add `$lisp-error` exception tag definition to type section in `src/clysm/compiler/codegen/gc-types.lisp`

**Checkpoint**: Foundation ready - user story implementation can begin

---

## Phase 3: User Story 1 - Compile Multiple Value Returns (Priority: P1) ðŸŽ¯ MVP

**Goal**: Fix 18 `values` compilation failures by debugging AST dispatch

**Independent Test**: Compile `(values 1 2 3)` and verify Wasm correctly sets mv-count=3, stores values in mv-buffer, returns primary value on stack

**HyperSpec**: [values](resources/HyperSpec/Body/f_values.htm)

### Tests for User Story 1

> **NOTE: Write tests FIRST, ensure they FAIL before implementation**

- [ ] T008 [P] [US1] Contract test for zero values `(values)` in `tests/contract/values-contract.lisp`

- [ ] T010 [P] [US1] Contract test for multiple values `(values a b c)` in `tests/contract/values-contract.lisp`
- [ ] T011 [P] [US1] Contract test for non-tail position values in `tests/contract/values-contract.lisp`

- [ ] T014 [US1] Debug `compile-to-instructions` dispatch for `ast-values` type in `src/clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section.lisp`
- [ ] T015 [US1] Fix any edge cases in `compile-values` at `src/clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section.lisp:12930`
- [ ] T016 [US1] Run `wasm-tools validate` on output for all values test cases
- [ ] T017 [US1] Verify 18 compiler forms using `values` now compile successfully

**Checkpoint**: User Story 1 complete - `values` forms compile correctly

---

## Phase 4: User Story 2 - Compile Type Declarations (Priority: P1)

**Goal**: Fix 18 `the` compilation failures by verifying AST pass-through dispatch

**Independent Test**: Compile `(the fixnum x)` and verify Wasm compiles successfully with x value returned

**Independent Test**: Compile `(labels ((a () (b)) (b () (a))) (a))` and verify both functions call each other correctly

### Implementation for User Story 4

- [ ] T050 [US4] Add `ast-handler-case` to `compile-to-instructions` etypecase dispatch
- [ ] T051 [US4] Run `wasm-tools validate` on output for all handler-case test cases
- [ ] T052 [US4] Verify 3 compiler forms using `handler-case` now compile successfully

**Checkpoint**: User Story 4 complete - exception handling works (45/45 failures resolved)

## Phase 7: Polish & Cross-Cutting Concerns

**Purpose**: Final validation and cleanup
